  title        = {Local lattice distortion in high-entropy alloys},
  year         = {2017},
  month        = {Jul},
  pages        = {023404},
  volume       = {1},
  comment      = {Alloys0: HfNbZr, HfNbTiZr, HfNbTaTiZr, NbTiV, AlNbTiV
Props0: Local lattice distortions, Elastic properties

Alloys1: CoFeNi, CoCrFeNi, CoCrFeMnNi
Props1: Local lattice distortions, Elastic properties, Magnetic properties

local lattice distortion (LLD)
similar local atomic environment (SLAE): No SQS
CASTEP
PBE, DLM (supercell)
"the atomic size mismatch evaluated with the empirical atomic radii is not accurate enough to describe the local lattice distortion"
"the local lattice distortion has negligible effect on the equilibrium lattice parameter and bulk modulus.", which is consistent with the finding of Koermann \cite{RN526}.
"local lattice distortion of the refractory HEAs is much more significant than that of the 3d HEAs"

"However, for some alloys $\delta$ calculated with the elemental or the 12-coordinated atomic radii cannot predict correctly the local lattice distortions"
" The lattice distortion energies of the refractory HEAs are in general substantially higher than those for the 3d HEAs ranging from 0.392 kJ/mol for CoCrFeMnNi to 1.858 kJ/mol for CoCrFeNi."

"This indicates that the equilibrium volume and bulk modulus are mainly determined by the compositions of the alloys and the first-principles methods in combination with the mean-field approximation such as coherent potential approximation to describe the randomness of the alloy can be safely used to predict these properties [37,38]."

SLAEの利点とは？
SQSがtotalとしてのrandomnessを考えているのに対し，SLAEはlocalのrandomnessを考えている．
結果として，SLAEはtotalとしてのrandomnessを多かれ少なかれ犠牲にしているはず．
実際のHEAは，SROを持っているはずなので，SQSもSLAEも必ずしも良い近似とは限らない．
また，SLAEでは，entropyが最大化されているわけではないはず．

YI:I think their SLAE model in Song et al. is actually just a variation of SQS (nothing is conceptually different from the SQS idea)
So I do not want to put a special weight on that here.},
